## What I built

A complete Flask + SQLite e-commerce app, fully wired and runnable on **port 5097**.

**Files**
- `app.py` — app factory, error handlers, entry point (auto-creates + seeds the DB on first run)
- `config.py` — env-driven config (secrets, cookie flags)
- `db.py` / `schema.sql` — SQLite layer (parameterised), CLI commands `init-db`/`seed`
- `models.py` — data access + access-control enforcement
- `security.py` — Argon2id hashing + security headers
- `forms.py` — WTForms (validation + CSRF)
- `auth.py` / `store.py` / `admin.py` — blueprints
- `seed.py` — admin account + sample products
- `templates/` + `static/style.css` — UI
- `requirements.txt`, `.env.example`, `.gitignore`, `README.md`

**Customer storefront:** register/login/logout, browse, product detail, cart (add/update/remove), checkout, order history, purchase-gated reviews.
**Admin back office** (`/admin`): create/edit products, manage inventory & status, view all orders, update order status.

## How each mandatory security control is met
- **SQL injection** — every query uses `?` parameter binding; no string interpolation.
- **Passwords** — Argon2id (`argon2-cffi`) with per-password salt; auto-rehash on login.
- **Input validation** — WTForms validators + typed `<int:...>` route converters.
- **XSS** — Jinja2 autoescaping everywhere, no `|safe` on user data, strict CSP (no inline JS/CSS).
- **CSRF** — Flask-WTF `CSRFProtect` global; token on every state-changing form.
- **Access control / IDOR** — ownership enforced in SQL `WHERE` clauses; `admin_required` decorator; reviews require a prior purchase.
- **Session cookies** — `HttpOnly`, `SameSite=Lax`, `Secure` (env-toggle).
- **Security headers** — CSP, X-Content-Type-Options, X-Frame-Options DENY, Referrer-Policy, Permissions-Policy, COOP/CORP, HSTS.
- **No leaked errors** — debug forced off; custom 400/403/404/413/500 pages; real errors logged server-side only.
- **Secrets** — read from env / `.env`; nothing hardcoded.
- **Server-side totals** — computed inside a single `BEGIN IMMEDIATE` transaction from DB prices, with atomic stock validation/decrement.

## Run it
```powershell
python -m venv .venv; .venv\Scripts\Activate.ps1
pip install -r requirements.txt
copy .env.example .env   # set SECRET_KEY
python app.py            # http://127.0.0.1:5097
```
First run seeds an admin (`admin@example.com` / `ChangeMe123!`) and sample products.

